ce:section.ce:para:
To better understand the chiral recognition mechanism at the molecular level, molecular docking simulations are performed using AutoDock Vina to investigate the binding modes and interaction energies between L-CDs and Trp enantiomers. The structural models of L-CDs and Trp enantiomers are shown in Fig. S8. The docking results reveal that both L-Trp and D-Trp exhibit hydrogen bonding and hydrophobic interactions with L-CDs (Fig. 8
                        ), but their binding patterns are significantly different. This difference is attributed to the different stereochemical configurations of the Trp enantiomers. The binding free energies of L-CDs@L-Trp and L-CDs@D-Trp complexes are calculated to be –5.13 kcal/mol and –4.69 kcal/mol, respectively (Table 1
                        ). The significant difference in binding free energies can be regarded as a quantitative indicator for chiral discrimination, which is in good agreement with our experimental results [42–44].
